  <tr><th>Category</th><th>Entries</th><th>Prose surface today</th><th>Fit as a normative home</th></tr>
  <tr><td>Blocks</td><td>81 (39 active / 30 draft / 12 concept)</td><td><code>block-descriptions/&lt;id&gt;.njk</code> partials (83) — real explainer prose + contract tables</td><td>Could host a section, but heterogeneous with the other three</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Intents</td><td>98 (6 active / 57 draft / 35 concept)</td><td>Inline HTML <code>description</code> field in the JSON entry — JSON-only by rule</td><td><strong>Statute-barred</strong>: <code>#intents-ux-only</code> forbids conformance/technical content in the intent description</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Plugs</td><td>59 (31 active / 26 concept / 2 experimental)</td><td>Registry entry <em>plus</em> a gate-required <code>plug-descriptions/&lt;id&gt;.njk</code> (59 exist — the "bare 10-line stub" premise was wrong); most already carry a TypeScript interface block</td><td>Could host a section</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Protocols</td><td>41 (0 active / 14 draft / 27 concept)</td><td>No partial dir — normative body lives in the owning project page under a stable <code>protocol-&lt;id&gt;</code> anchor</td><td>Scattered across project pages; no per-standard document</td></tr>
